--- a/packaging/docker/README.md
+++ b/packaging/docker/README.md
@@ -1,5 +1,7 @@
 # hivebox Docker
 
+Hivebox is the container alternative to installed local mode. It deliberately keeps the Rails source at `/app/web`, durable state under `/data`, and GitHub first-login/owner authentication. For a loopback-only, no-login UI over your existing local repositories, install the gem and run `hive setup` instead; the two modes do not share storage conventions or auth defaults.
+
 ## Install (golden path)
 
 One command on any machine with Docker.
