-# hivebox web
+# Hive web
 
-The hivebox operator UI — a vanilla Rails 8 + Turbo app served by `hive web`
-(see `wiki/commands/web.md`). Operator docs live in `packaging/docker/README.md`;
-architecture decisions in `wiki/decisions.md` (ADR-036/ADR-037).
+The Rails 8 + Turbo operator UI is shared by two supported modes:
+
+- Installed local mode: run `hive setup` in a real repository, then open `http://127.0.0.1:4567`. Bare `hive web` stays foreground; `hive web install|start|status|restart|tail|stop` manages the separate per-user unit. It uses the same XDG registry/queue and repository `.hive-state` as the CLI/TUI, with no login gate on literal loopback only.
+- Docker/hivebox: the supervisor runs the source app at `/app/web`, stores durable state under `/data`, and explicitly selects GitHub owner auth. See [the Docker guide](../packaging/docker/README.md).
+
+The installed gem contains production Rails source, while bundle/assets/cache/log/PID/SQLite writes go to Hive-owned XDG paths. `hive setup` is the repair path for missing or stale runtime state. Non-loopback local binds require `--github-auth` or explicit `--unsafe-no-auth`; an occupied port is reported rather than silently changed.
+
+Implementation details live in [wiki/commands/web.md](../wiki/commands/web.md); architecture decisions in [wiki/decisions.md](../wiki/decisions.md) (ADR-036/ADR-037).
